BLOEMFONTEIN - The Free State Cheetahs had some good news this week when they revealed they had signed an exciting new winger Makazole Mapimpi from the Southern Kings.Mapimpi made his Vodacom Cup debut for Border in 2014 against the Sharks XV and was a star performer in their final match of the 2015 season against Boland Cavaliers when he scored a hat-trick of tries.READ: Cheetahs name Francois Venter as captainHe also took over the kicking duties and slotted three conversions and a penalty in the absence of the regular kicker.He made his Currie Cup debut for Border against the Griquas in 2014 and has seen action for the Kings in this year s Super Rugby campaign. African News Agency